&lt;p&gt;Nurse AHP Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West Hertfordshire community respiratory service provided by CLCH is looking for an enthusiastic forward thinking nurse specialist to join our integrated Covid19 Follow Up Service. The post holder will provide patient centered integrated care&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;to patients discharged from Watford Hospital with Covid19, or to those patients referred directly by primary care. The post holder will work within a dedicated Covid19 follow up team, led by an 8a, situated within the wider community respiratory service. They will provide a virtual holistic assessment service, identify patient problems related to Covid19 and signpost them onto other relevant community services, whilst continuing working closely with our integrated partners, the Respiratory Consultants at West Herts Hospitals Trust. Effective communication skills, attendance at MDTs and audit and data entry will be a key components of the role. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust (CLCH) works across London and Hertfordshire, and is rated Good by the Care Quality Commission. We’re also in the HSJ best places to work list and in Stonewall’s top employers index.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community healthcare is our focus and our passion. We champion the role of community health professionals to make sure our patients get great care closer to home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maria Buxton MSc, Grad Dip Phys&lt;br /&gt;Consultant Respiratory Physiotherapist &amp; Service Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
